One speedster claimed to be an Eskom employee who was “dealing with load shedding issues”. The Ekurhuleni Metropolitan Police Department’s High Speed Unit arrested the four on Sunday between 5am and 11am on the stretch of the N3 freeway southbound between the Geldenhuys Interchange and the Rand Airport turn-off. This stretch of the freeway is a 120km/h zone. The drivers were caught doing speeds of between 162km/h and 173km/h. 